257
00:23:44,708 --> 00:23:46,875
then it needs
to be terminated.

258
00:23:46,958 --> 00:23:48,666
And without hesitation.

259
00:23:48,750 --> 00:23:50,750
Yes, Colonel.

260
00:23:50,833 --> 00:23:52,333
This school is
your last chance.

261
00:23:52,416 --> 00:23:54,291
If trash like yourselves
can't keep up

262
00:23:54,375 --> 00:23:57,208
with the academic ability of
regular students, this is it!

263
00:23:57,291 --> 00:23:59,916
If you can't live a decent
social life, you end up here

264
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:02,750
and if you screw up here,
it's the end of the road!

265
00:24:02,833 --> 00:24:04,750
Also, even though
you're under fiften,

266
00:24:04,833 --> 00:24:07,291
if you get more than fifty
penalty points on your record

267
00:24:07,375 --> 00:24:09,000
you're sent to the
regular corps.

268
00:24:09,083 --> 00:24:11,541
Eh bite me. Don't mess
with us you bald old goat.

269
00:24:11,625 --> 00:24:13,000
Are any of you listening?

270
00:24:13,083 --> 00:24:14,541
You lost me
halfway through, sir!

271
00:24:14,625 --> 00:24:19,500
Discipline! Discipline!
Discipline! Discipline!

272
00:24:19,583 --> 00:24:24,000
Discipline!
Discipline! Dismissed!

273
00:24:24,083 --> 00:24:26,750
Thank you very much, sir.

274
00:24:28,875 --> 00:24:31,333
Ya loser! You and me are
gonna go at it someday, Jack!

275
00:24:31,416 --> 00:24:33,458
We're gonna remember
this buddy!

276
00:24:34,250 --> 00:24:37,083
Yeah ya sick mother! Damn.

277
00:24:41,208 --> 00:24:41,791
Uh, ya sure?

278
00:24:41,875 --> 00:24:43,875
Look hey!

279
00:24:43,958 --> 00:24:45,500
Yamagata why'd they
keep you so long?

280
00:24:45,583 --> 00:24:47,291
Kaneda what happened
to your cheek?

281
00:24:47,375 --> 00:24:48,500
I heard you got into a fight.

282
00:24:48,583 --> 00:24:50,083
So what?

283
00:24:50,166 --> 00:24:51,666
My friend told me. Yeah, they
told me you faught the Clowns

284
00:24:51,750 --> 00:24:52,791
in the old city.

285
00:24:52,875 --> 00:24:54,375
Big deal.

286
00:24:54,458 --> 00:24:56,375
Why don't you just wipe 'em all
out? Those guys are so gross.

287
00:24:56,458 --> 00:24:58,750
Clowns, there were
demonstrators, cops,

288
00:24:58,833 --> 00:25:01,958
the damn army, and that idiot
Tetsuo had an accident.

289
00:25:02,041 --> 00:25:04,041
But what happened to Tetsuo?

290
00:25:04,125 --> 00:25:05,833
Huh? He's in the hospital
but we don't know where.

291
00:25:05,916 --> 00:25:09,041
Dumb loser was
tryin' a show off.

292
00:25:11,166 --> 00:25:12,416
Stupid idiot.

293
00:25:12,500 --> 00:25:14,333
You're talking
about Tetsuo right?

294
00:25:14,416 --> 00:25:16,500
Shut up already. Why do ya
always have to be hanging

295
00:25:16,583 --> 00:25:17,750
on my arm every minute?

296
00:25:17,833 --> 00:25:19,500
What tha heck
has gotten into you?

297
00:25:32,666 --> 00:25:33,875
Huh?

298
00:25:35,291 --> 00:25:37,166
Tetsuo? It's time
for your medication.

299
00:25:39,291 --> 00:25:41,625
Doctor hurry! The boy is gone.

300
00:25:45,916 --> 00:25:48,958
No I can't. You know the
dorm mother always throws a fit

301
00:25:49,041 --> 00:25:50,708
if you go out before ten.

302
00:25:50,791 --> 00:25:53,583
Yeah, you know the one
who has a face like a goat?

303
00:25:53,666 --> 00:25:55,666
That woman is such
a big ol' pain.

304
00:25:55,750 --> 00:25:57,625
She's always complaining
about us girls.

305
00:25:57,708 --> 00:26:00,416
Huh? Tomorrow at three?
Yeah that's cool.

306
00:26:00,500 --> 00:26:03,041
Hey, what happened
to that girl? You know who.

307
00:26:03,125 --> 00:26:04,750
After my friend saw him.

308
00:26:04,833 --> 00:26:07,500
I don't like her at all.
Her attitude gets on my nerves.

309
00:26:08,250 --> 00:26:08,625
Kaori.

310
00:26:08,708 --> 00:26:10,125
What tha?

311
00:26:11,458 --> 00:26:13,208
Tetsuo you're here.

312
00:26:14,250 --> 00:26:17,916
Everyone's been worried about
you. They thought you were dead.

313
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:29,541
When I woke up, I was on an
operating table or something.

314
00:26:29,625 --> 00:26:32,750
That examination--it's
like they were messing

315
00:26:32,833 --> 00:26:35,083
around inside my head.

316
00:26:35,166 --> 00:26:39,666
No, I don't wanna go back
there again. We'll run away.

317
00:26:39,750 --> 00:26:41,416
Where would we go to?

318
00:26:43,125 --> 00:26:47,333
I dunno. Someplace.
Someplace far away.

319
00:26:51,500 --> 00:26:53,416
Hey it's self study today!

320
00:26:54,750 --> 00:26:58,291
Where'd the teacher go to?
What about my burning desire

321
00:26:58,375 --> 00:27:01,458
to study and learn a vocation?
Well drag his butt in here.

322
00:27:01,541 --> 00:27:05,125
Ah! Kaneda hurry,
come quick your bike!

323
00:27:05,208 --> 00:27:06,250
What about my bike?

324
00:27:06,333 --> 00:27:09,208
See? Look it. Down there.

325
00:27:11,625 --> 00:27:13,875
Wha? Tetsuo?

326
00:27:16,250 --> 00:27:17,416
Is this ok?

327
00:27:17,500 --> 00:27:19,583
Ah quiet. Shut up and hang on.

328
00:27:31,750 --> 00:27:32,208
Huh? What tha?

329
00:27:32,291 --> 00:27:33,583
What's wrong?

330
00:27:35,333 --> 00:27:36,541
Aww Jesus Christ

331
00:27:36,625 --> 00:27:39,666
Uh oh, we're stopping now.

332
00:27:39,750 --> 00:27:40,958
We've stopped.

333
00:27:42,375 --> 00:27:45,041
Oh I get it, the engine
can't drop below 5000 rpms,

334
00:27:45,125 --> 00:27:46,333
even when
you're changing the gears.

335
00:27:46,416 --> 00:27:48,458
Oh ouch. My butt hurts.

336
00:27:48,541 --> 00:27:50,291
Hey, look. Some bikes!

337
00:27:51,041 --> 00:27:54,166
Is that Kaneda and-- Wha?

338
00:27:54,250 --> 00:27:55,625
No it isn't!

339
00:27:57,291 --> 00:27:59,500
Shit! Kaori!

340
00:28:03,375 --> 00:28:04,666
Any sign of them?

341
00:28:04,750 --> 00:28:07,166
Huata and the others
went to look around Kizenyazu.

342
00:28:07,250 --> 00:28:10,458
The only place we have to search
now is the industrial area.

343
00:28:10,541 --> 00:28:12,208
K. Let's go!

344
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:18,291
We owe you for the other night.
Now it's time for payback.

345
00:28:26,875 --> 00:28:28,375
Shut up!

346
00:28:30,708 --> 00:28:32,750
Kaori! What happened?

347
00:28:40,166 --> 00:28:43,583
No, don't! If you put so much as
a single scratch on that bike

348
00:28:43,666 --> 00:28:45,333
I'm gonna kill your ass.

349
00:28:45,416 --> 00:28:48,416
Hahaha. Huh?

350
00:28:50,750 --> 00:28:52,416
Run!

351
00:28:52,500 --> 00:28:54,041
After them!

352
00:29:00,541 --> 00:29:01,875
No, wait.

353
00:29:03,416 --> 00:29:04,458
Huh?

354
00:29:11,875 --> 00:29:13,250
Tetsuo!

355
00:29:29,958 --> 00:29:32,458
You're gonna kill him,
Tetsuo. You want that?

356
00:29:32,541 --> 00:29:33,833
I want him more than dead.

357
00:29:33,916 --> 00:29:35,583
I want to split
his friggin head open.

358
00:29:35,666 --> 00:29:38,083
Just knock it off now.
This whole thing happened

359
00:29:38,166 --> 00:29:40,375
just because you took
my bike for a spin.

360
00:29:40,458 --> 00:29:42,041
Enough already.

361
00:29:42,125 --> 00:29:46,208
Shut up! Don't order me around!

362
00:29:46,291 --> 00:29:47,833
We were just worried.

363
00:29:47,916 --> 00:29:51,666
Why do ya always have
to try and save me?

364
00:29:51,750 --> 00:29:54,750
I coulda handled it
on my own. Ya I admit,

365
00:29:54,833 --> 00:29:56,583
I gotten beaten before,

366
00:29:56,666 --> 00:29:59,666
but I won't always be on the
receiving end. You hear that?

367
00:29:59,750 --> 00:30:01,500
You understand?

368
00:30:06,250 --> 00:30:07,666
Tetsuo.

369
00:30:08,708 --> 00:30:10,500
Shut up, go away.

370
00:30:13,166 --> 00:30:15,833
Hey wait! Where are you going?

371
00:30:17,083 --> 00:30:18,625
Leave me alone.

372
00:30:20,625 --> 00:30:21,875
Akira!

373
00:30:25,916 --> 00:30:27,166
Tetsuo!

374
00:30:30,166 --> 00:30:32,250
Something wrong?

375
00:30:32,333 --> 00:30:33,166
Akira.

376
00:30:33,250 --> 00:30:37,250
I don't know who that is! Ah!

377
00:30:57,833 --> 00:30:59,666
Tetsuo... what's wrong?

378
00:30:59,750 --> 00:31:01,250
A-Are you alright?

379
00:31:06,041 --> 00:31:08,500
This is really strange.
I'm getting a blue pattern

380
00:31:08,583 --> 00:31:10,375
on scope number three.

381
00:31:10,458 --> 00:31:13,708
What? No!
Retrieve the subject now, hurry.

382
00:31:27,625 --> 00:31:30,416
Why don't you guys
just leave my friend alone?

383
00:31:33,791 --> 00:31:37,208
What's with the getup, huh?
You going to a funeral?

384
00:31:44,208 --> 00:31:45,416
Tetsuo!

385
00:31:46,333 --> 00:31:47,416
Kaneda!

386
00:31:48,958 --> 00:31:50,000
Screw you! Huh?

387
00:31:59,416 --> 00:32:00,625
No wait!

388
00:32:06,458 --> 00:32:08,666
Kaneda, what the hell's
goin on?

389
00:32:19,083 --> 00:32:22,500
Well well, I see we have
some real hip youngsters

390
00:32:22,583 --> 00:32:25,041
doing their thing
inspite of the tight checkpoints

391
00:32:25,125 --> 00:32:26,583
they got going around tonight.

392
00:32:26,666 --> 00:32:30,041
And that just means that they're
all pretty stupid, don't it?

393
00:32:30,125 --> 00:32:34,791
Huh? Oh whatever.
This is boring.

394
00:32:34,875 --> 00:32:37,041
Hey, whaddya say.
Let's go home.

395
00:32:37,125 --> 00:32:39,583
Wah? But it's still early.

396
00:32:39,666 --> 00:32:41,333
Yeah, but without their bikes

397
00:32:41,416 --> 00:32:43,750
they're just tail chasers
outta water.

398
00:32:43,833 --> 00:32:45,250
You mean fish.

399
00:32:45,333 --> 00:32:48,083
Come on, lets go
and toss these fish back.

400
00:32:48,166 --> 00:32:51,666
Hey, Kaneda!
Aww what are we gonna do?

401
00:32:54,375 --> 00:32:55,791
What tha heck?

402
00:32:55,875 --> 00:32:56,958
Look.

403
00:33:23,125 --> 00:33:24,291
It's that girl.

404
00:33:24,375 --> 00:33:25,791
Here we go again.

405
00:33:25,875 --> 00:33:28,833
Look lets get out of here
before we get caught up in it.

406
00:33:28,916 --> 00:33:31,708
Huh? Kaneda?

407
00:33:31,791 --> 00:33:32,958
Hey!

408
00:33:34,541 --> 00:33:37,500
This area is being corded off
due to a terrorist bombing.

409
00:33:37,583 --> 00:33:40,208
Those who wish to get through
line up single file,

410
00:33:40,291 --> 00:33:43,125
present your ID, and precede
through the checkpoint.

411
00:33:54,416 --> 00:33:55,541
Get in.

412
00:33:55,625 --> 00:33:58,041
What's wrong? Hurry!
I'll meet ya shortly.

413
00:34:00,041 --> 00:34:01,708
You know the
rendezvous point, right?

414
00:34:03,041 --> 00:34:03,791
Be careful

415
00:34:03,875 --> 00:34:06,250
You too. You be careful.

416
00:34:19,583 --> 00:34:21,208
Hey! Hold it right there.

417
00:34:23,708 --> 00:34:25,000
She's got a gun!

418
00:34:36,875 --> 00:34:40,250
Ok that's far enough.
Alright? Drop it.

419
00:34:48,333 --> 00:34:49,583
Drop it!

420
00:34:55,375 --> 00:34:56,708
Don't do it!

421
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:14,541
I think it came from over here.
There were two shots, no three.

422
00:35:14,625 --> 00:35:16,208
It's just up ahead.

423
00:35:16,291 --> 00:35:19,791
Hey, let's get out of here.
Come on!

424
00:36:26,833 --> 00:36:28,166
Kaneda!

425
00:36:53,458 --> 00:36:57,791
There. Now, what's the matter?
Talk about it.

426
00:36:57,875 --> 00:37:00,583
It was a dream that I saw.

427
00:37:00,666 --> 00:37:03,625
A dream?

428
00:37:03,708 --> 00:37:08,958
The city started to crumble
apart covered by a big shadow.

429
00:37:09,041 --> 00:37:11,166
And lots of people died.

430
00:37:11,250 --> 00:37:15,083
And the three of us,
we get to meet Akira again.

431
00:37:15,166 --> 00:37:17,208
Wha-- Akira?

432
00:37:17,291 --> 00:37:23,916
The city will crumble. So many
people. So many will die.

433
00:37:24,916 --> 00:37:28,500
When will it happen?
Do you know when? Kiyoko!

434
00:37:28,583 --> 00:37:34,291
You mustn't let that boy go.
His power-- it--

435
00:37:40,750 --> 00:37:42,000
What's she talking about?

436
00:37:42,083 --> 00:37:45,541
Well, there's a-- Uhh...
there seems to be nothing

437
00:37:45,625 --> 00:37:49,958
physically wrong with her and
her medication looks accurate.

438
00:37:50,041 --> 00:37:51,666
There's no sign
of any abnormalities

439
00:37:51,750 --> 00:37:54,500
in her EKG or EEG either.

440
00:37:54,583 --> 00:37:57,000
I think Number 25's
statement is probably

441
00:37:57,083 --> 00:38:00,041
her precognitive power at work.

442
00:38:00,125 --> 00:38:01,291
You know, this needs to be

443
00:38:01,375 --> 00:38:03,583
brought before
the supreme council for inquiry.

444
00:38:04,958 --> 00:38:06,208
Do you believe her?

445
00:38:06,291 --> 00:38:08,833
I have no doubts regarding
Number 25's abilities.

446
00:38:08,916 --> 00:38:12,166
We've lots of data
that substantiates it.

447
00:38:12,250 --> 00:38:14,208
What do you believe, Colonel?

448
00:38:14,291 --> 00:38:17,458
I'll tell you my job
isn't to believe or disbelieve.

449
00:38:17,541 --> 00:38:19,500
It's to act or not act.

450
00:38:28,833 --> 00:38:30,416
Of course there are
several security measures

451
00:38:30,500 --> 00:38:32,208
before we enter.

452
00:38:32,291 --> 00:38:33,666
Here sir.

453
00:38:33,750 --> 00:38:37,250
Cold gear, Colonel. Please
put it on. You too, Doctor.

454
00:38:48,916 --> 00:38:50,750
The other day
a young researcher

455
00:38:50,833 --> 00:38:52,750
came to me
and asked me something.

456
00:38:54,375 --> 00:38:57,166
He wondered if their power was
the form of the next stage

457
00:38:57,250 --> 00:38:59,958
that human evolution was taking
and purhaps we would all

458
00:39:00,041 --> 00:39:02,333
be able to control it someday.

459
00:39:02,416 --> 00:39:05,708
Hmph. Scientists are
a bunch of romantics.

460
00:39:05,791 --> 00:39:07,583
Military men on the other
hand always consider

461
00:39:07,666 --> 00:39:09,333
the risks first.

462
00:39:09,416 --> 00:39:13,416
Over thirty years
it's taken. We've come so far,

463
00:39:13,500 --> 00:39:15,500
crawling up from the rubble.

464
00:39:15,583 --> 00:39:18,250
We can't just trade one
for the other.

465
00:39:18,333 --> 00:39:19,750
But I've always
thought that you've held

466
00:39:19,833 --> 00:39:23,083
a resentment--even a hatred--
for this city, Colonel.

467
00:39:23,166 --> 00:39:25,125
The passion to build is cool

468
00:39:25,208 --> 00:39:27,541
and the joy of
reconstruction forgotten.

469
00:39:27,625 --> 00:39:30,208
Now-- Now it's just
a garbage heap made up of

470
00:39:30,291 --> 00:39:32,625
a bunch of hedonistic fools.

471
00:39:32,708 --> 00:39:36,333
But inspite of that
you're trying to save the city.

472
00:39:36,416 --> 00:39:40,083
I'm not a scientist.
I think like a soldier.

473
00:39:43,750 --> 00:39:46,625
Colonel? We're here sir.
This way please.

474
00:40:07,666 --> 00:40:11,166
Room ten. 148 degrees Kelvin.

475
00:40:11,250 --> 00:40:14,291
Fluctuation tolerance range?
Check.

476
00:40:14,375 --> 00:40:18,125
Room nine 108 degrees Kelvin.
Fluctuation tolerance range,

477
00:40:18,208 --> 00:40:19,125
check.

478
00:40:19,208 --> 00:40:21,291
Emergency power generator.
Check.

479
00:40:21,375 --> 00:40:22,208
Open the door.

480
00:40:22,291 --> 00:40:24,083
Sir. Uh...

481
00:40:24,166 --> 00:40:25,208
The control room. Do it!

482
00:40:25,291 --> 00:40:26,458
Yes, sir!

483
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:49,333
Room one is at 0.0005 degrees
Kelvin. It's within tolerances.

484
00:40:49,416 --> 00:40:52,000
No abnormalities detected
within any of the rooms,

485
00:40:52,083 --> 00:40:54,833
duar walls,
or defense systems.

486
00:40:54,916 --> 00:40:58,708
No abnormal reactions
or concentrations recorded.

487
00:40:58,791 --> 00:41:00,833
So then all systems are nominal.

488
00:41:10,208 --> 00:41:13,666
Look at what they abandoned in
their panic. They were afraid.

489
00:41:13,750 --> 00:41:16,166
They were too scared so they
hid it away from the public,

490
00:41:16,250 --> 00:41:18,666
losing all sense
of shame and honor,

491
00:41:18,750 --> 00:41:22,041
casting aside the civilization,
and abandoning the science

492
00:41:22,125 --> 00:41:23,541
that created it.

493
00:41:23,625 --> 00:41:25,166
Shutting the lid
of the pandora's box

494
00:41:25,250 --> 00:41:27,333
they themselves had opened.

495
00:41:30,583 --> 00:41:32,541
Hey, we're still young.
We could start over again.

496
00:41:32,625 --> 00:41:33,625
Ryu?!

497
00:41:33,708 --> 00:41:35,000
So whaddya think, huh?

498
00:41:35,083 --> 00:41:36,250
Ryu!

499
00:41:36,333 --> 00:41:38,166
That's the first time
you killed a man, right?

500
00:41:38,250 --> 00:41:39,458
Come on, I'll go with you.

501
00:41:39,541 --> 00:41:40,625
Ryu!

502
00:41:40,708 --> 00:41:42,250
You aren't listening.
Turn yourself in.

503
00:41:42,333 --> 00:41:44,333
I'll even go to
the police station with you.

504
00:41:44,416 --> 00:41:45,458
Ryu!

505
00:41:45,541 --> 00:41:48,041
Anyway, when you
get out I'll be there.

506
00:41:48,125 --> 00:41:50,250
Let's go out
for drinks, alright?

507
00:41:50,333 --> 00:41:53,500
Don't kick yourself over it.
What's done is done.

508
00:41:53,583 --> 00:41:54,666
You've heard that.

509
00:41:54,750 --> 00:41:57,250
The guy is dead and gone. Huh?

510
00:42:02,625 --> 00:42:04,833
Huh? Identify yourselves.

511
00:42:04,916 --> 00:42:05,750
Yaa--

512
00:42:05,833 --> 00:42:08,625
Ryu. Are you alright?

513
00:42:08,708 --> 00:42:09,666
Kay, it's you.

514
00:42:09,750 --> 00:42:11,500
Ryu.

515
00:42:11,583 --> 00:42:13,458
Who's this.

516
00:42:13,541 --> 00:42:17,875
Huh? Who's this? Well, I guess
by saying I'm Kay's boyfriend

517
00:42:17,958 --> 00:42:19,791
it's stretching it a bit.

518
00:42:19,875 --> 00:42:22,333
Depends on your point
of view. But we haven't gotten

519
00:42:22,416 --> 00:42:23,708
physical or anything.

520
00:42:23,791 --> 00:42:24,708
You understand, don't you?

521
00:42:24,791 --> 00:42:25,458
Are you a spy?

522
00:42:25,541 --> 00:42:26,000
No I'm not.

523
00:42:26,083 --> 00:42:26,750
You're lying!

524
00:42:26,833 --> 00:42:28,291
Ahhh!

525
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:33,458
Well, is he a spy or not?

526
00:42:33,541 --> 00:42:36,083
Whatever he is
he's certainly not a spy.

527
00:42:37,625 --> 00:42:39,000
Ow.

528
00:42:40,416 --> 00:42:43,708
Sneak into their lab,
that's crazy! Ridiculous!

529
00:42:43,791 --> 00:42:45,291
Remember the fiasco
with that kid?!

530
00:42:45,375 --> 00:42:48,916
They're last minute orders, and
the plan is in place already.

531
00:42:51,833 --> 00:42:54,875
These are the lab passes
they issue once a week.

532
00:42:54,958 --> 00:42:56,875
From Mr. Nezu, right?

533
00:42:56,958 --> 00:42:58,333
What's the objective?

534
00:42:58,416 --> 00:43:01,041
We're to gather detailed data
on the new subject.

535
00:43:01,125 --> 00:43:02,916
You're kidding, a new subject?

536
00:43:03,000 --> 00:43:06,250
Yes, last week. On the same
night we tried to abduct

537
00:43:06,333 --> 00:43:09,583
the experimental subject
they call Number 26.

538
00:43:09,666 --> 00:43:12,541
A boy who was in an accident
on an old city highway

539
00:43:12,625 --> 00:43:14,041
was brought to the lab.

540
00:43:14,125 --> 00:43:16,666
It seems he's a student at
a vocational training school,

541
00:43:16,750 --> 00:43:19,791
but now he's their new subject
for human experimentation.

542
00:43:19,875 --> 00:43:21,333
Huh?

543
00:43:26,541 --> 00:43:29,458
Hey hey hey hey hey!
What's the big idea?

544
00:43:29,541 --> 00:43:30,458
Uh! Kaneda!

545
00:43:30,541 --> 00:43:32,458
Should I kill him?
He heard us.

546
00:43:32,541 --> 00:43:33,708
Ryu!

547
00:43:33,791 --> 00:43:35,666
Wait! Now just hold on
a minute. Hear me out.

548
00:43:35,750 --> 00:43:37,000
Please listen to
what I have to say.

549
00:43:37,083 --> 00:43:38,416
Ryu, he did save me.

550
00:43:38,500 --> 00:43:39,500
Yeah, twice!

551
00:43:39,583 --> 00:43:41,458
Maybe he did it
just to get close to us.

552
00:43:41,541 --> 00:43:43,583
The guy who was in that
accident in the old city

553
00:43:43,666 --> 00:43:45,125
is a close friend of mine.

554
00:43:45,208 --> 00:43:46,916
I know it's hard for you
to believe what I'm saying

555
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:48,125
but it's the truth.

556
00:43:48,208 --> 00:43:51,041
I was right there
right when it happened.

557
00:43:51,125 --> 00:43:53,500
Come on. Don't they say
the only foolish questions

558
00:43:53,583 --> 00:43:57,583
are unasked ones?
Huh? They don't?

559
00:43:59,250 --> 00:44:02,541
That's an intriging story now,
isn't it?

560
00:44:02,625 --> 00:44:05,375
Well, will you be taking
the boy with you?

561
00:44:05,458 --> 00:44:07,291
He knows the subject.
And I think we could use him

562
00:44:07,375 --> 00:44:10,000
as a decoy if
we find it necessary.

563
00:44:10,083 --> 00:44:12,708
New Tokyo's going
to change soon.

564
00:44:15,500 --> 00:44:18,166
In all respects this
city is saturated.

565
00:44:18,250 --> 00:44:20,250
It's like an overripe fruit.

566
00:44:20,333 --> 00:44:23,333
Buried within it is a new seed.
We need only wait for the wind

567
00:44:23,416 --> 00:44:26,166
which would make it
fall to fruitition.

568
00:44:26,250 --> 00:44:29,416
 The wind called Akira.

569
00:44:29,500 --> 00:44:33,125
Ryu. Look over here.

570
00:44:33,208 --> 00:44:34,583
What is it?

571
00:44:34,666 --> 00:44:37,416
We arent the ones who will
change this. But rather it's

572
00:44:37,500 --> 00:44:40,708
those citizens that hope
for Akira that will.

573
00:44:40,791 --> 00:44:42,916
That which is called science
perverts providence.

574
00:44:43,000 --> 00:44:46,333
That which is called progress
encourages extravagance.

575
00:44:46,416 --> 00:44:48,333
That which is called
civilization devastates

576
00:44:48,416 --> 00:44:49,916
the spirit of man.

577
00:44:50,000 --> 00:44:54,041
The time of atonement is upon
us. Are your hearts prepared?

578
00:44:54,125 --> 00:44:58,125
The time is nigh! The time
of his awakening is night!

579
00:44:58,208 --> 00:45:01,625
The moment of Lord Akira's
awakening is drawing closer.

580
00:45:01,708 --> 00:45:04,125
Are your hearts and minds
prepared for a new coming?

581
00:45:04,208 --> 00:45:08,000
Break it up. Holding
meetings here is prohibited.

582
00:45:08,083 --> 00:45:10,125
This gathering is illegal!

583
00:45:11,666 --> 00:45:15,166
Terrorist activities carried
out by antigovernment elements

584
00:45:15,250 --> 00:45:17,333
have skyrocketed this month.

585
00:45:17,416 --> 00:45:19,958
The army, riot squad,
and even traffic police

586
00:45:20,041 --> 00:45:23,000
have fully mobilized.
The overtime costs alone

587
00:45:23,083 --> 00:45:25,041
have used up the
public safety budget.

588
00:45:25,125 --> 00:45:27,083
And then there's the
abduction of Number 26.

589
00:45:27,166 --> 00:45:28,458
Isn't their existence
supposed to be

590
00:45:28,541 --> 00:45:30,625
the highest of state
secrets, Colonel?

591
00:45:30,708 --> 00:45:34,291
No one's ever heard of peace and
order here in Neo Tokyo-land?

592
00:45:34,375 --> 00:45:38,458
And this, this request of
yours for further-- ah yes,

593
00:45:38,541 --> 00:45:42,541
for further funding because of
subject number 25's prediction.

594
00:45:42,625 --> 00:45:43,208
Well that's--

595
00:45:43,291 --> 00:45:44,708
You must be joking!

596
00:45:44,791 --> 00:45:46,583
While straightening out the
historic tax reform blunders

597
00:45:46,666 --> 00:45:48,250
of our former Prime Minister,

598
00:45:48,333 --> 00:45:50,583
we parliament members have
been bowing our heads down

599
00:45:50,666 --> 00:45:52,291
and begging the public
to bear with us

600
00:45:52,375 --> 00:45:54,833
and what does
he ask for? Money.

601
00:45:54,916 --> 00:45:58,000
Where exactly do we get
that kind of money?

602
00:45:58,083 --> 00:45:59,708
We've already spend a fortune
here and all we have

603
00:45:59,791 --> 00:46:02,708
to show for it is that grotesque
kindergarten you've set up.

604
00:46:02,791 --> 00:46:05,333
The Olympics are next near and
the post-war period is over,

605
00:46:05,416 --> 00:46:06,875
how much longer will
you keep throwing away

606
00:46:06,958 --> 00:46:09,166
countless amounts of money
on these worthless ghosts?

607
00:46:09,250 --> 00:46:11,291
I always said we should
put all that money into

608
00:46:11,375 --> 00:46:12,458
the welfare program

609
00:46:12,541 --> 00:46:13,416
Shut up old man!

610
00:46:13,500 --> 00:46:13,958
What was that?

611
00:46:14,041 --> 00:46:15,500
You heard me!

612
00:46:15,583 --> 00:46:16,916
Now listen here. That power
is starting to walk around free

613
00:46:17,000 --> 00:46:18,416
as we speak.

614
00:46:18,500 --> 00:46:21,583
Unless we control that power
now we'll lose everything

615
00:46:21,666 --> 00:46:22,875
we've tried so hard to achieve.

616
00:46:22,958 --> 00:46:24,208
You're about to take
that old man comment back!

617
00:46:24,291 --> 00:46:25,958
It was your lack of policy
that started this mess

618
00:46:26,041 --> 00:46:27,500
in the first place!

619
00:46:27,583 --> 00:46:29,416
There is still no proof that
the last world war was caused

620
00:46:29,500 --> 00:46:31,583
by Akira in my opinion.

621
00:46:31,666 --> 00:46:34,208
Don't you understand?
Unless an Akira disaster

622
00:46:34,291 --> 00:46:37,666
actually happens-- Don't you
people understand anything?

623
00:46:37,750 --> 00:46:40,875
Has anyone ever seen
this Number 26 Akira?

624
00:46:40,958 --> 00:46:42,083
You're wrong!

625
00:46:43,625 --> 00:46:45,125
Break it up!

626
00:46:45,208 --> 00:46:47,875
I say that the Colonel has lost
sight of his duty as a soldier.

627
00:46:47,958 --> 00:46:51,041
Yes, he's right! And I
have had several reports.

628
00:46:51,125 --> 00:46:53,125
Reports on
antigovernment elements.

629
00:46:53,208 --> 00:46:55,208
How they're using your
Akira madness to ramp up

630
00:46:55,291 --> 00:46:57,000
their terrorist ferver.

631
00:46:57,083 --> 00:46:58,875
That's not true. It's just not.

632
00:46:58,958 --> 00:47:01,625
Then what about that Akira
World Renewal movement?

633
00:47:01,708 --> 00:47:04,125
Wouldn't you say that
information's being leaked?

634
00:47:04,208 --> 00:47:07,125
World Renewal Movement? It's
more like the end of the world.

635
00:47:07,208 --> 00:47:09,875
Aren't you just using Akira
as camoflage to cover up

636
00:47:09,958 --> 00:47:11,333
your misconduct? Admit it!

637
00:47:11,416 --> 00:47:13,208
What are you getting at?

638
00:47:13,291 --> 00:47:16,500
Colonel. Please be calm
and try to understand

639
00:47:16,583 --> 00:47:19,458
that we can no longer leave
the peace of Neo Tokyo

640
00:47:19,541 --> 00:47:22,791
to your sole discretion.
Understood?

641
00:47:22,875 --> 00:47:26,458
I'm sorry, but you're to be put
before an inquiry committee.

642
00:47:26,541 --> 00:47:29,000
You and the whole military
needs a reform!

643
00:47:31,375 --> 00:47:32,166
Excuse me.

644
00:47:32,250 --> 00:47:33,250
What?

645
00:47:34,833 --> 00:47:36,916
This discussion isn't over.

646
00:47:37,000 --> 00:47:38,000
This is an outrage. 

647
00:47:38,083 --> 00:47:38,708
You should explain yourself!

648
00:47:38,791 --> 00:47:40,125
How dare you walk--

649
00:47:40,208 --> 00:47:41,833
Are you trying to insult
the supreme executive council?

650
00:47:41,916 --> 00:47:43,583
His behavior is intolerable!

651
00:48:06,750 --> 00:48:08,833
Need-Need water

652
00:48:41,958 --> 00:48:44,750
Hey, wait a minute! Let's see...

653
00:48:44,833 --> 00:48:47,541
Isn't that cable replacement
due for next week?

654
00:48:47,625 --> 00:48:51,208
Well, the cable they ordered
came in a whole week early.

655
00:48:51,291 --> 00:48:53,625
And besides, I got
vacation time coming

656
00:48:53,708 --> 00:48:55,375
and I'm leaving this weekend,

657
00:48:55,458 --> 00:48:58,875
but if I bring the workers back
there'll be overtime.

658
00:48:58,958 --> 00:49:00,666
I could leave now
and come back but

659
00:49:00,750 --> 00:49:03,083
the work's gotta be
done sooner or later.

660
00:49:08,416 --> 00:49:09,791
Alright guys, let's go.

661
00:50:40,666 --> 00:50:41,583
What tha--?

662
00:50:53,333 --> 00:50:54,458
What tha hell?

663
00:51:11,500 --> 00:51:13,833
It's milk! Wh-Wha--?

664
00:51:19,250 --> 00:51:22,041
Stay away! No!

665
00:51:28,333 --> 00:51:29,958
Ahhh!

666
00:51:35,208 --> 00:51:36,458
It's blood.

667
00:51:36,541 --> 00:51:38,333
I'm scared.

668
00:51:46,458 --> 00:51:48,375
Weirdo.

669
00:51:48,458 --> 00:51:51,291
Those kids... who are they?

670
00:52:43,416 --> 00:52:45,875
Huh? Hmmm.

671
00:52:45,958 --> 00:52:51,833
Patient room 887. Shema, Tetsuo.
Oh! The automatic lock's off.

672
00:52:56,875 --> 00:53:00,166
Hey you! You're not
allowed to leave your room!

673
00:53:03,583 --> 00:53:07,125
See to it. There,
we'll find another room.

674
00:53:07,208 --> 00:53:09,458
Get a load of the room.
Looks like a tornado hit it.

675
00:53:09,541 --> 00:53:10,916
Look at all that glass!

676
00:53:32,583 --> 00:53:34,291
There are 58 blocks
with circuits that

677
00:53:34,375 --> 00:53:36,208
the computer will display.

678
00:53:36,291 --> 00:53:38,166
Of those, nearly 40
are concentrated

679
00:53:38,250 --> 00:53:40,125
on underground levels
seven and eight.

680
00:53:40,208 --> 00:53:41,916
That's probably the place.

681
00:53:44,666 --> 00:53:47,083
The central wiring shaft
should be straight up ahead.

682
00:53:47,166 --> 00:53:51,166
We'll be able to use that to go
straight down to the sub levels.

683
00:53:51,250 --> 00:53:54,708
Be careful.
It's deeper in the middle.

684
00:53:54,791 --> 00:53:56,291
Hoo, what a stink.

685
00:53:56,375 --> 00:53:58,083
Don't you ever stop talking?

686
00:53:58,166 --> 00:54:00,333
What? I said it stinks
because it stinks.

687
00:54:00,416 --> 00:54:01,458
Is your nose
busted or something?

688
00:54:01,541 --> 00:54:03,125
Keep up and be quiet.

689
00:54:04,791 --> 00:54:07,208
Damn. Hug the walls.

690
00:54:07,291 --> 00:54:08,916
Huh? What are you guys doing?

691
00:54:09,000 --> 00:54:10,375
You idiot, get down!

692
00:54:25,333 --> 00:54:26,583
They left?

693
00:54:26,666 --> 00:54:28,250
Looks like they beefed up
security, doesn't it?

694
00:54:28,333 --> 00:54:29,583
Must be that siren we heard.

695
00:54:29,666 --> 00:54:31,375
Ryu, can you scout
a way around it?

696
00:54:31,458 --> 00:54:33,000
No, I wanna check out
the security at the very least.

697
00:54:33,083 --> 00:54:34,583
Hey are you ok?

698
00:54:34,666 --> 00:54:37,083
Let's keep going.

699
00:54:37,166 --> 00:54:39,458
Damn they spotted us!
Run for it!

700
00:54:39,541 --> 00:54:40,833
Turn back you bastards!

701
00:54:40,916 --> 00:54:42,875
Shu! Hold your fire!

702
00:54:47,458 --> 00:54:51,041
Shumazaki! Ugh. You assholes.

703
00:54:51,125 --> 00:54:53,041
Forget it! Run!

704
00:54:56,958 --> 00:54:58,625
What the hell
is that thing huh?

705
00:55:00,333 --> 00:55:01,166
Go!

706
00:55:01,250 --> 00:55:02,750
Huh? He's dead.

707
00:55:02,833 --> 00:55:04,250
Let it go.

708
00:55:09,375 --> 00:55:11,583
Die!

709
00:55:11,666 --> 00:55:15,041
This is Unit 304 Shaft Ditch.
I have encountered intruders.

710
00:55:15,125 --> 00:55:17,833
Requesting backup.
Now engaging.

711
00:55:17,916 --> 00:55:19,083
Here he comes!

712
00:55:44,791 --> 00:55:46,041
Uh! Kay!

713
00:55:48,791 --> 00:55:50,833
Dammit. The gun!

714
00:55:55,541 --> 00:55:56,708
Kaneda!

715
00:56:06,666 --> 00:56:08,625
Kay, over here!

716
00:56:08,708 --> 00:56:10,750
Huh? Now!

717
00:56:13,000 --> 00:56:14,750
Kaneda come on! Hurry!

718
00:56:30,041 --> 00:56:31,166
Kaneda no!

719
00:56:44,541 --> 00:56:47,875
What the hell? Where are
the brakes? That's not it.

720
00:56:47,958 --> 00:56:50,500
I-- This is the central
wiring shaft, I think.

721
00:56:50,583 --> 00:56:52,000
I can't figure it out.

722
00:56:52,083 --> 00:56:53,291
What the--?

723
00:56:58,000 --> 00:57:00,416
There now,
that's right. Behave.

724
00:57:00,500 --> 00:57:03,000
Ask the Colonel for clearance
on the use of firearms.

725
00:57:03,083 --> 00:57:04,500
Hey turn the radio up.

726
00:57:05,583 --> 00:57:07,208
There must be some
kind of mistake here.

727
00:57:07,291 --> 00:57:09,916
That boy looks like the patient
they admitted over in the lab.

728
00:57:10,000 --> 00:57:12,166
Correct. The boy is a
psychic named Tetsuo Shima.

729
00:57:12,250 --> 00:57:14,916
He broke out of his ward. He's
headed for the baby room!

730
00:57:15,000 --> 00:57:16,333
It's Tetsuo?

731
00:57:16,416 --> 00:57:18,791
He's extremely dangerous.
Do not let him through.

732
00:57:18,875 --> 00:57:20,875
I repeat, do not
let him through.

733
00:57:58,625 --> 00:58:00,708
It's no use hiding any more.

734
00:58:00,791 --> 00:58:03,333
We have no choice then.
Use your guns.

735
00:58:03,416 --> 00:58:04,875
We can't let him
go any further.

736
00:58:04,958 --> 00:58:07,583
No matter what it takes. Fire!

737
00:58:48,166 --> 00:58:50,375
Good. All here, are you?

738
00:58:56,166 --> 00:58:57,625
Stop it!

739
00:58:59,666 --> 00:59:02,125
So how long are you
gonna keep playing around?

740
00:59:09,208 --> 00:59:11,625
Where's the other one
hiding, huh?

741
00:59:11,708 --> 00:59:13,708
Hey you, you're a creton.

742
00:59:13,791 --> 00:59:15,000
Huh?

743
00:59:15,083 --> 00:59:16,333
Die!

744
00:59:19,125 --> 00:59:20,583
Takashi!

745
00:59:31,458 --> 00:59:36,083
What the hell is going on
with me? Am I dreaming?

746
00:59:36,166 --> 00:59:40,250
These powers... are they real
or just an hallucination?

747
00:59:46,875 --> 00:59:49,375
Dammit where the hell
am I going? Where?

748
00:59:49,458 --> 00:59:52,833
Proceed straight.
Proceed straight ahead.

749
00:59:52,916 --> 00:59:54,083
Huh?

750
00:59:54,166 --> 00:59:56,458
You'll find
a freight elevator just ahead.

751
00:59:58,250 --> 01:00:01,166
You can take it down
to sublevel eight.

752
01:00:09,166 --> 01:00:12,208
That's good.
You're all together.

753
01:00:12,291 --> 01:00:16,916
You thought you could kill me?
I'm through with it.

754
01:00:17,000 --> 01:00:21,458
You tried to mess with me
and now I'm gonna kill you.

755
01:00:21,541 --> 01:00:22,750
Huh?

756
01:00:26,750 --> 01:00:29,208
You were there. I remember.

757
01:00:29,291 --> 01:00:30,250
Takashi! 

758
01:00:30,333 --> 01:00:31,083
Huh?

759
01:00:31,166 --> 01:00:32,625
Together, let's attack him!

760
01:00:32,708 --> 01:00:34,375
Uh, uh huh.

761
01:00:39,208 --> 01:00:40,833
You little twerps!

762
01:00:57,250 --> 01:00:58,875
All of you, that is enough!

763
01:01:07,708 --> 01:01:09,708
Who the hell are you?

764
01:01:12,375 --> 01:01:16,041
Huh? What's the matter?
Is your head hurting?

765
01:01:16,125 --> 01:01:19,041
Tetsuo Shima, your power
isn't fully matured yet.

766
01:01:19,125 --> 01:01:22,000
If you push yourself
you might do irreparable damage.

767
01:01:22,083 --> 01:01:23,291
We can help.

768
01:01:23,375 --> 01:01:26,333
What the hell? What.. did...
you people... do?

769
01:01:26,416 --> 01:01:27,875
You messed with my head.

770
01:01:36,166 --> 01:01:38,333
